{"title": "Goldman Sachs to raise headcount in asset and wealth management as it expands in Asia", "tags": "business", "timestamp": "2024-04-25", "content": "SINGAPORE - Asia, including Singapore, is an important part of Goldman Sachs\u2019 global game plan to grow its asset and wealth management and the bank will hire \u201csteadily\u201d in this space as it woos institutions and the super wealthy.\nMr Marc Nachmann, its global head of asset and wealth management, told The Straits Times on April 22 that Singapore, Australia and Hong Kong are very important wealth markets in the region for the Wall Street bank, along with Dubai, home to the second-largest number of wealthy Indian diaspora after the US."}